A businessman and car dealer, Alhaji Surajo Yandaki and one Sani Chambe both of Yandaki village in Kaita LGA of Katsina state have been reportedly kidnapped last night. Sources told Daily Trust that the abductors stormed the town about 2am on Thursday and broke down their residences before whisking them away. The police are not readily available for comment as at the time of filing this report but family sources said the abductors are yet to reach out to the family. Details later… Kidnapped  Katsina girl freed after ‘ransom’ Kidnappers demand N100m for 11-year-old girl Gunmen kidnap ex-LG chair’s daughter